<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 6:31PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Meriwether, eastern
Heard, Troup and Coweta Counties through 700 PM EDT...
At 631 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Odessadale, or near
Greenville, moving west at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Newnan, LaGrange, Greenville, Senoia, Hogansville, Grantville,
Luthersville, Moreland, Sharpsburg, Turin, Haralson, Lone Oak, Gay,
East Newnan, Corinth, Mountville, Louise, Odessadale, Stovall and
Harrisonville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
